# Site Configuration

The `site.json` file is the heart of your Zyros website. This comprehensive guide covers all available configuration options.

## File Structure

Your `site.json` file should be located in the `public/` directory and follows this basic structure:

```json
{
  "site": { /* Site metadata */ },
  "header": { /* Header configuration */ },
  "footer": { /* Footer configuration */ },
  "contentBlocks": [ /* Reusable content blocks */ ],
  "forms": [ /* Form definitions */ ],
  "pages": [ /* Your site pages */ ]
}
```

## Site Configuration

### Basic Settings
```json
{
  "site": {
    "title": "Your Site Title",
    "description": "Site description for SEO",
    "author": "Your Name",
    "url": "https://yoursite.com",
    "language": "en",
    "favicon": "/favicon.svg",
    "theme": "light"
  }
}
```

### Social Links
```json
{
  "site": {
    "social": {
      "twitter": "https://twitter.com/yourusername",
      "github": "https://github.com/yourusername",
      "linkedin": "https://linkedin.com/in/yourusername",
      "email": "hello@yoursite.com"
    }
  }
}
```

### SEO Configuration
```json
{
  "site": {
    "seo": {
      "keywords": ["keyword1", "keyword2"],
      "ogImage": "/og-image.jpg",
      "twitterCard": "summary_large_image"
    }
  }
}
```

### Feature Toggles
```json
{
  "site": {
    "features": {
      "search": true,
      "newsletter": false,
      "comments": false,
      "darkMode": true,
      "analytics": true,
      "socialShare": true,
      "tableOfContents": true,
      "readingProgress": true
    }
  }
}
```

## Header Configuration

### Logo Setup
```json
{
  "header": {
    "logo": {
      "text": "Site Name",
      "image": "/logo.png",
      "url": "/",
      "size": "medium",
      "position": "left"
    }
  }
}
```

### Navigation Menu
```json
{
  "header": {
    "navigation": [
      {
        "title": "Home",
        "href": "/",
        "icon": "üè†"
      },
      {
        "title": "Products",
        "href": "#",
        "icon": "üì¶",
        "children": [
          {
            "title": "Product A",
            "href": "/product-a"
          },
          {
            "title": "Product B",
            "href": "/product-b"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Header Styling
```json
{
  "header": {
    "sticky": true,
    "transparent": false,
    "style": "modern",
    "height": "normal",
    "background": {
      "type": "blur"
    },
    "border": {
      "show": true,
      "style": "solid"
    }
  }
}
```

## Page Configuration

### Basic Page Structure
```json
{
  "pages": [
    {
      "title": "Page Title",
      "slug": "page-url",
      "description": "Page description for SEO",
      "category": "blog",
      "tags": ["tag1", "tag2"],
      "publishedAt": "2024-01-20",
      "readingTime": 5,
      "layout": "default",
      "content": "# Page Content\n\nYour markdown content here..."
    }
  ]
}
```

### Layout Options
- `default` - Standard blog layout
- `minimal` - Clean, distraction-free
- `full-width` - Edge-to-edge content
- `sidebar` - Content with sidebar
- `landing` - Optimized for conversions
- `portfolio` - Project showcase
- `documentation` - Technical docs

### Custom Fields
```json
{
  "customFields": {
    "featured": true,
    "priority": "high",
    "showContactForm": true,
    "customCSS": ".custom { color: red; }"
  }
}
```

## Content Blocks

Reusable sections that can be referenced in pages:

```json
{
  "contentBlocks": [
    {
      "id": "hero-main",
      "type": "hero",
      "title": "Welcome",
      "subtitle": "Subtitle",
      "content": "Hero content",
      "data": {
        "buttons": [
          {
            "text": "Get Started",
            "href": "/start",
            "style": "primary"
          }
        ]
      },
      "visible": true
    }
  ]
}
```

## Forms Configuration

```json
{
  "forms": [
    {
      "id": "contact",
      "title": "Contact Us",
      "description": "Get in touch",
      "fields": [
        {
          "id": "name",
          "type": "text",
          "label": "Name",
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "email",
          "type": "email",
          "label": "Email",
          "required": true
        }
      ],
      "submitText": "Send",
      "action": "/api/contact"
    }
  ]
}
```

## Environment Variables

For sensitive data, use environment variables:

```bash
# .env.local
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://yoursite.com
GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID=GA_MEASUREMENT_ID
EMAIL_SERVICE_API_KEY=your_api_key
```

## Validation

Validate your configuration:

```bash
# Check for errors
zyros validate

# Detailed validation report
zyros validate --detailed
```

## Best Practices

### Performance
- Keep the site.json file under 1MB
- Optimize images and use appropriate formats
- Use content blocks for repeated sections

### SEO
- Always include page descriptions
- Use meaningful slugs and titles
- Add relevant keywords and tags

### Maintenance
- Use consistent naming conventions
- Comment complex configurations
- Version control your site.json

---

*Need help with a specific configuration? Check our [API Reference](/api) or ask in our [Discord community](https://discord.gg/zyros).*
